    # ===== Original Image and Histogram =====
    plot_image_histogram(img, "Original Image")

    # ===== Histogram Equalization =====
    hist_eq = cv2.equalizeHist(img)
    plot_image_histogram(hist_eq, "Histogram Equalized Image")

    print("ℹ️ Histogram equalization spreads out intensity values and improves image contrast.")

    # ===== Spatial Filtering =====
    kernel_size = 5
    avg_filtered = cv2.blur(img, (kernel_size, kernel_size))
    gauss_filtered = cv2.GaussianBlur(img, (kernel_size, kernel_size), 0)
    median_filtered = cv2.medianBlur(img, kernel_size)

    plt.figure(figsize=(15,8))

    plt.subplot(2,3,1)
    plt.imshow(img, cmap='gray')
    plt.title("Original Image")
    plt.axis('off')

    plt.subplot(2,3,2)
    plt.imshow(avg_filtered, cmap='gray')
    plt.title(f"Averaging Filter ({kernel_size}x{kernel_size})")
    plt.axis('off')

    plt.subplot(2,3,3)
    plt.imshow(gauss_filtered, cmap='gray')
    plt.title(f"Gaussian Filter ({kernel_size}x{kernel_size})")
    plt.axis('off')

    plt.subplot(2,3,4)
    plt.imshow(median_filtered, cmap='gray')
    plt.title(f"Median Filter ({kernel_size}x{kernel_size})")
    plt.axis('off')

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

    # ===== Frequency Domain Filtering (Low-Pass Filter) =====
    f = np.fft.fft2(img)
    fshift = np.fft.fftshift(f)

    rows, cols = img.shape
    crow, ccol = rows//2, cols//2

    mask = np.zeros((rows, cols), np.uint8)
    radius = 30 # radius of low-pass filter
    cv2.circle(mask, (ccol, crow), radius, 1, thickness=-1)

    # Apply mask in frequency domain
    fshift_filtered = fshift * mask

    # Inverse FFT to get back to spatial domain
    f_ishift = np.fft.ifftshift(fshift_filtered)
    img_back = np.fft.ifft2(f_ishift)
    img_back = np.abs(img_back)
    img_back = np.uint8(img_back)

    # ===== Display Result =====
    plt.figure(figsize=(12,5))

    plt.subplot(1,2,1)
    plt.imshow(img, cmap='gray')
    plt.title("Original Image")
    plt.axis('off')

    plt.subplot(1,2,2)
    plt.imshow(img_back, cmap='gray')
    plt.title("Low Pass Filtered Image (Freq Domain)")
    plt.axis('off')

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
